{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b4a8a0f5-0769-43f4-b750-31a9795d553d","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nKey notes:\n- **xUnit** is the outlier — skip is a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute.\n- All four frameworks will report skipped tests (not silent passes), so you'll see them in test results as a reminder to re-enable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7284364d-296e-400a-babd-8c3ce127d691","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":344,"requestId":"083D:1AA32E:80A63FD:8EFB153:69EAC2A3"},"id":"e9df24ff-fa22-4523-8786-623766cf1565","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:08:59.928Z","parentId":"2e4e7bc4-348f-4b90-879d-dbfe4e109a3e"}
